.\" dug.1 - macOS-native DNS lookup utility
.Dd April 17, 2026
.Dt DUG 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm dug
.Nd macOS-native DNS lookup utility using the system resolver
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Ar @server
.Op Ar +flags
.Op Ar -flags
.Op Ar name
.Op Ar type
.Op Ar class
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
is a DNS lookup utility for macOS that uses the system resolver
.Pq mDNSResponder
by default, showing what applications actually see.
Unlike
.Xr dig 1 ,
which always sends queries directly to nameservers,
.Nm
reveals the full resolution path: which network interface handled the query,
whether the answer came from cache, and which nameservers were configured.
.Pp
When features require direct DNS access
.Pq such as @server, +tcp, or +dnssec ,
.Nm
automatically falls back to sending queries directly using libresolv.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Ss Output Flags
.Bl -tag -width "+traditional" -compact
.It Cm +short
One rdata value per line.
.It Cm +traditional
dig-compatible output with section headers.
.It Cm +noall
Suppress all output sections. Combine with
.Cm +answer ,
.Cm +authority ,
etc. to show specific sections.
.It Cm +answer
Show the answer section.
.It Cm +authority
Show the authority section.
.It Cm +additional
Show the additional section.
.It Cm +question
Show the question section.
.It Cm +stats
Show query statistics
.Pq time, server .
.It Cm +cmd
Show the command line echo.
.It Cm +nocmd
Suppress the command line echo.
.El
.Ss Behavioral Flags
.Bl -tag -width "+norecurse" -compact
.It Cm +tcp Pq or +vc
Use TCP instead of UDP. Triggers direct DNS.
.It Cm +dnssec
Request DNSSEC records
.Pq RRSIG, DNSKEY, DS .
Triggers direct DNS because mDNSResponder consumes these records internally.
.It Cm +norecurse
Send a non-recursive query
.Pq clear the RD bit .
Triggers direct DNS.
.It Cm +cd
Set the Checking Disabled flag.
.It Cm +adflag
Set the Authenticated Data flag.
.It Cm +time= Ns Ar N
Query timeout in seconds
.Pq 1\(en300, default 5 .
.It Cm +tries= Ns Ar N
Total query attempts
.Pq 1\(en10, default 3 .
.It Cm +retry= Ns Ar N
Retries after first attempt
.Pq 0\(en10 .
.It Cm +search
Use the search list from resolver configuration.
.It Cm +validate
Probe DNSSEC validation via the system resolver with a 2-second timeout.
.It Cm +why
Print resolver selection reason to stderr.
.El
.Ss Dash Flags
.Bl -tag -width "-c CLASS" -compact
.It Fl x Ar address
Reverse DNS lookup for an IPv4 or IPv6 address.
.It Fl p Ar port
Query on a non-standard port
.Pq default 53 .
Triggers direct DNS.
.It Fl t Ar type
Explicit record type.
.It Fl c Ar class
Explicit query class
.Pq IN, CH, HS, ANY .
.It Fl q Ar name
Explicit domain name.
.It Fl 4
Force IPv4 transport. Triggers direct DNS.
.It Fl 6
Force IPv6 transport. Triggers direct DNS.
.El
.Ss Record Types
A, AAAA, MX, NS, SOA, CNAME, TXT, SRV, PTR, CAA, HTTPS, ANY.
Specify as a positional argument or with
.Fl t .
Numeric types
.Pq e.g., TYPE65
are also accepted.
.Sh OUTPUT FORMAT
.Nm
has three output modes:
.Bl -tag -width "+traditional"
.It Default (enhanced)
Shows dig-style sections plus system-resolver-specific metadata:
interface name, cache status, DNSSEC validation status, and resolver
configuration. Includes a SYSTEM RESOLVER PSEUDOSECTION and RESOLVER SECTION.
.It Cm +traditional
dig-compatible output with HEADER, QUESTION, ANSWER, AUTHORITY, and
ADDITIONAL sections. Meaningful with direct DNS which provides authority
and additional sections.
.It Cm +short
One rdata value per line. No headers, no comments.
.El
.Sh RESOLVER MODES
.Ss System Resolver (default)
Queries go through mDNSResponder, the macOS system resolver. This is the
same path applications use, so
.Nm
shows the actual resolution behavior including split DNS, VPN routing,
and local cache.
.Ss Direct DNS (automatic fallback)
Certain flags require sending queries directly to nameservers. When any of
these are present,
.Nm
falls back to direct DNS via libresolv:
.Pp
.Cm @server , +tcp , +dnssec , +cd , +adflag , -p , -4 , -6 , +norecurse ,
non-IN class.
.Pp
Use
.Cm +why
to see which flag triggered the fallback.
.Sh DNSSEC
.Ss System Validation (+validate)
The
.Cm +validate
flag asks mDNSResponder to perform DNSSEC validation. It uses a 2-second
timeout because
.Fn kDNSServiceFlagsValidate
causes mDNSResponder to time out for domains on nameservers without DNSSEC
support.
.Ss Direct DNSSEC (+dnssec)
The
.Cm +dnssec
flag triggers direct DNS fallback because mDNSResponder consumes
RRSIG, DNSKEY, and DS records internally for its own validation and never
returns them to clients.
.Sh EXAMPLES
Look up A records:
.Dl dug example.com
.Pp
Look up MX records:
.Dl dug example.com MX
.Pp
Short output:
.Dl dug +short example.com
.Pp
Query a specific nameserver:
.Dl dug @8.8.8.8 example.com
.Pp
Reverse lookup:
.Dl dug -x 8.8.8.8
.Pp
Show only the answer section:
.Dl dug +noall +answer example.com
.Pp
dig-compatible output:
.Dl dug +traditional @8.8.8.8 example.com
.Pp
Use TCP:
.Dl dug +tcp example.com
.Pp
Request DNSSEC records:
.Dl dug +dnssec example.com
.Pp
Probe system DNSSEC validation:
.Dl dug +validate example.com
.Pp
See why a resolver mode was chosen:
.Dl dug +why +tcp example.com
.Pp
Query on a non-standard port:
.Dl dug -p 5353 @127.0.0.1 example.com
.Pp
IPv6 nameserver:
.Dl dug @2001:4860:4860::8888 example.com AAAA
.Sh COMPATIBILITY
.Nm
accepts most
.Xr dig 1
flags and produces similar output. Key differences:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
Default mode uses the system resolver, not direct DNS.
.It
Enhanced output includes system resolver metadata (interface, cache, DNSSEC status).
.It
.Cm +traditional
produces dig-compatible output.
.It
.Cm +validate
is dug-specific (system DNSSEC validation probe).
.It
.Cm +why
is dug-specific (resolver selection debugging).
.El
.Sh KNOWN ISSUES
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
macOS 26 has a resolver regression with non-IANA TLDs
.Pq .internal, .test, .lan .
.It
mDNSResponder consumes RRSIG/DNSKEY/DS records internally, so
.Cm +dnssec
must use direct DNS.
.It
.Cm +validate
times out for domains on nameservers without DNSSEC support.
.El
.Sh EXIT STATUS
.Bl -tag -width "XX" -compact
.It 0
Success. NXDOMAIN is not an error.
.It 1
Usage error
.Pq bad arguments .
.It 9
Query timed out.
.It 10
Internal or network error.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr dig 1 ,
.Xr dscacheutil 1 ,
.Xr scutil 8
